{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VR6nJBUdGJdFfgxRHSBf3G","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Frontend Patterns Report\n\nHere are the key frontend patterns in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/`:\n\n### 1. Session & Auth Context\n\n**Import Path:** `src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n\n**Key Hook:**\n```typescript\nexport function useSession(): SessionContextValue\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface SessionContextValue {\n  isAuthenticated: boolean;\n  isAuthenticating: boolean;\n  accessToken: string | null;\n  authenticate: () => Promise<string>;\n  clearSession: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { useSession } from \"./context/SessionContext\";\n\nconst { isAuthenticated, isAuthenticating, accessToken, authenticate, clearSession } = useSession();\n```\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- JWT-based authentication (sign-once challenge-response)\n- Automatic token refresh 5 minutes before expiry\n- Persisted sessions survive page reloads\n- Handles wallet connections and switches automatically\n- Provides `accessToken` for Bearer token requests\n\n**Provider Setup** (already in `main.tsx`):\n```typescript\n<WalletProvider>\n  <SessionProvider>\n    <App />\n  </SessionProvider>\n</WalletProvider>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Wallet Context\n\n**Import Path:** `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` (from `packages/wallet/src`)\n\n**Key Hook:**\n```typescript\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface WalletContextValue extends WalletState {\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  getBalance?: () => number;           // mock mode only\n  getBalanceLamports?: () => number;   // mock mode only\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void; // mock mode only\n}\n\ninterface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { useWallet } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n\nconst { \n  connected, \n  address, \n  publicKey, \n  signMessage, \n  sendTransaction,\n  isMock,\n  getBalance \n} = useWallet();\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Toast Notifications\n\n**Pattern:** No centralized toast library. Notifications are feature-specific state managed via context.\n\n**Example: Chest Drop Notification**\n\n**Component:** `src/features/quests/components/ChestDropNotification.tsx`\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nimport { useQuests } from \"../context/QuestsContext\";\n\nexport function ChestDropNotification() {\n  const { chestDropNotification } = useQuests();\n  \n  if (!chestDropNotification.visible) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  \n  return (\n    <div className=\"chest-drop-notification\">\n      {/* Notification UI */}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**CSS Classes:** `.chest-drop-notification` (in `src/index.css`, line 13582-13660)\n- `.chest-drop-notification__content`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__icon`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__text`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__title`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__subtitle`\n\n**Generic Toast Classes** (in `src/index.css`, line 3858-3890):\n```\n.rng-toast\n.rng-toast--success\n.rng-toast--error\n.rng-toast--warning\n.rng-toast--info\n```\n\n**Rendering Location:** `App.tsx` lines 372-373 — placed after `<MiniProfileModal />` in the top-level `<AppContent>`:\n```typescript\n<MiniProfileModal />\n<ChestDropNotification />\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Feature Hooks Pattern\n\n**Location:** `src/features/*/hooks/`\n\n**Pattern (Simple):**\n```typescript\n// features/coinflip/hooks/index.ts\nexport { useCoinflip } from \"../context/CoinflipContext\";\n```\n\n**Pattern (With Custom Data Fetching):**\n\n**Example: `src/features/player-profile/hooks/useSolPrice.ts`**\n```typescript\nexport function useSolPrice(): number | null {\n  const [price, setPrice] = useState<number | null>(null);\n  const intervalRef = useRef<ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null>(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    let cancelled = false;\n\n    async function fetchPrice() {\n      try {\n        const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/price/sol-usd`);\n        if (!res.ok) return;\n        const data: { price: number } = await res.json();\n        if (!cancelled) setPrice(data.price);\n      } catch {\n        // Graceful degradation — keep previous price or null\n      }\n    }\n\n    fetchPrice();\n    intervalRef.current = setInterval(fetchPrice, REFRESH_INTERVAL_MS);\n\n    return () => {\n      cancelled = true;\n      if (intervalRef.current) clearInterval(intervalRef.current);\n    };\n  }, []);\n\n  return price;\n}\n```\n\n**Example: `src/features/player-profile/hooks/useTransactions.ts`**\n```typescript\nexport function useTransactions(game?: string) {\n  const [transactions, setTransactions] = useState<Transaction[]>([]);\n  const [nextCursor, setNextCursor] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [loadingMore, setLoadingMore] = useState(false);\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchPage = useCallback(\n    async (cursor?: string) => {\n      const token = getAccessToken();\n      if (!token) {\n        setTransactions([]);\n        setLoading(false);\n        return;\n      }\n      // Fetch with JWT Bearer token\n      const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/profile/transactions?${qs}`, {\n        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n        signal: controller.signal,\n      });\n      // ...\n    },\n    [game],\n  );\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    fetchPage();\n    return () => abortRef.current?.abort();\n  }, [fetchPage]);\n\n  return { transactions, loading, loadingMore, error, nextCursor, loadMore };\n}\n```\n\n**Hook Export Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// features/player-profile/hooks/index.ts\nexport { usePlayerProfile, truncateAddress } from \"../context/PlayerProfileContext\";\nexport { useTransactions } from \"./useTransactions\";\nexport type { Transaction } from \"./useTransactions\";\nexport { useSolPrice } from \"./useSolPrice\";\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Context Provider Pattern\n\n**Example: `src/features/quests/context/QuestsContext.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\ninterface QuestsContextValue {\n  dailyQuests: QuestProgress[];\n  weeklyQuests: QuestProgress[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  dailyResetAt: number;\n  weeklyResetAt: number;\n  treasureChests: TreasureChest[];\n  unopenedChestCount: number;\n  claimableQuestCount: number;\n  chestDropNotification: ChestDropNotification;\n  claimQuestReward: (questId: string) => Promise<{ xp: number; chests: number }>;\n  openChest: (chestId: string) => Promise<ChestContents>;\n  openAllChests: () => Promise<ChestContents>;\n  // ... helper methods\n}\n\nexport function QuestsProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n  const { address } = useWallet(); // Access wallet address\n  \n  // State setup\n  const [dailyQuests, setDailyQuests] = useState<QuestProgress[]>([]);\n  // ... more state\n  \n  // Effects for loading and subscriptions\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!address) {\n      // Clear state when disconnected\n      return;\n    }\n    // Load data\n  }, [address]);\n  \n  const value: QuestsContextValue = { /* ... */ };\n  return (\n    <QuestsContext.Provider value={value}>\n      {children}\n    </QuestsContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\nexport function useQuests(): QuestsContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(QuestsContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useQuests must be used within QuestsProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Import Paths\n\n| Pattern | Import Path |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Session (auth, JWT) | `src/context/SessionContext` — `useSession()` |\n| Wallet (address, signing) | `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` — `useWallet()` |\n| Quests (main feature) | `src/features/quests` — `useQuests()`, `QuestsProvider` |\n| Profile (transactions, SOL price) | `src/features/player-profile/hooks` — `useTransactions()`, `useSolPrice()` |\n| Coinflip game | `src/features/coinflip` — `useCoinflip()` |\n| Toast CSS | `src/index.css` — `.rng-toast*` classes (line 3858+) |\n| Notification rendering | `src/App.tsx` AppContent — `<ChestDropNotification />` (line 372) |\n\n---\n\n### Key Patterns & Gotchas\n\n1. **Feature hooks live in `features/*/hooks/index.ts`** — they re-export from context or export custom data-fetching hooks\n2. **Contexts always check wallet connection** via `const { address } = useWallet()` and clear state when address is null\n3. **JWT token access:** Use `getAccessToken()` from `src/lib/auth-store` in custom hooks for Bearer tokens\n4. **Toasts are state-based, not imperative** — use context state to control visibility, not a toast library\n5. **Notifications are mounted globally in `App.tsx`** — not local to features\n6. **All contexts wrap error checking** — throw descriptive error if used outside provider\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/context/QuestsContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/hooks/useTransactions.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/hooks/useSolPrice.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx` (main layout)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9e6baade8de9c0bb (use SendMessage with to: 'a9e6baade8de9c0bb' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 62584\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 88352</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e340fd0-3e08-4923-9328-61b8592b2652","uuid":"41663ba0-5552-45a7-8073-4f52b5b9b562","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:01:35.419Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the frontend patterns for:\n1. Session/auth context - how `useSession()` works, what it provides (accessToken, isAuthenticated, etc.)\n2. Wallet context - how `useWallet()` works, what it provides (address, etc.)\n3. Toast notifications - how to show toasts in this app\n4. Existing hooks pattern in the features folder\n\nSearch in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/` for:\n- SessionContext or useSession\n- useWallet (the app's wallet hook, not the adapter one)\n- toast or notification patterns\n- Any existing feature hooks in `features/*/hooks/`\n\nProvide the key imports and patterns I need to use. Be thorough - show me the exact import paths and function signatures.","agentId":"a9e6baade8de9c0bb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Frontend Patterns Report\n\nHere are the key frontend patterns in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/`:\n\n### 1. Session & Auth Context\n\n**Import Path:** `src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n\n**Key Hook:**\n```typescript\nexport function useSession(): SessionContextValue\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface SessionContextValue {\n  isAuthenticated: boolean;\n  isAuthenticating: boolean;\n  accessToken: string | null;\n  authenticate: () => Promise<string>;\n  clearSession: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { useSession } from \"./context/SessionContext\";\n\nconst { isAuthenticated, isAuthenticating, accessToken, authenticate, clearSession } = useSession();\n```\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- JWT-based authentication (sign-once challenge-response)\n- Automatic token refresh 5 minutes before expiry\n- Persisted sessions survive page reloads\n- Handles wallet connections and switches automatically\n- Provides `accessToken` for Bearer token requests\n\n**Provider Setup** (already in `main.tsx`):\n```typescript\n<WalletProvider>\n  <SessionProvider>\n    <App />\n  </SessionProvider>\n</WalletProvider>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Wallet Context\n\n**Import Path:** `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` (from `packages/wallet/src`)\n\n**Key Hook:**\n```typescript\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue\n```\n\n**Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface WalletContextValue extends WalletState {\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  getBalance?: () => number;           // mock mode only\n  getBalanceLamports?: () => number;   // mock mode only\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void; // mock mode only\n}\n\ninterface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { useWallet } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n\nconst { \n  connected, \n  address, \n  publicKey, \n  signMessage, \n  sendTransaction,\n  isMock,\n  getBalance \n} = useWallet();\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Toast Notifications\n\n**Pattern:** No centralized toast library. Notifications are feature-specific state managed via context.\n\n**Example: Chest Drop Notification**\n\n**Component:** `src/features/quests/components/ChestDropNotification.tsx`\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nimport { useQuests } from \"../context/QuestsContext\";\n\nexport function ChestDropNotification() {\n  const { chestDropNotification } = useQuests();\n  \n  if (!chestDropNotification.visible) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  \n  return (\n    <div className=\"chest-drop-notification\">\n      {/* Notification UI */}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**CSS Classes:** `.chest-drop-notification` (in `src/index.css`, line 13582-13660)\n- `.chest-drop-notification__content`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__icon`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__text`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__title`\n- `.chest-drop-notification__subtitle`\n\n**Generic Toast Classes** (in `src/index.css`, line 3858-3890):\n```\n.rng-toast\n.rng-toast--success\n.rng-toast--error\n.rng-toast--warning\n.rng-toast--info\n```\n\n**Rendering Location:** `App.tsx` lines 372-373 — placed after `<MiniProfileModal />` in the top-level `<AppContent>`:\n```typescript\n<MiniProfileModal />\n<ChestDropNotification />\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Feature Hooks Pattern\n\n**Location:** `src/features/*/hooks/`\n\n**Pattern (Simple):**\n```typescript\n// features/coinflip/hooks/index.ts\nexport { useCoinflip } from \"../context/CoinflipContext\";\n```\n\n**Pattern (With Custom Data Fetching):**\n\n**Example: `src/features/player-profile/hooks/useSolPrice.ts`**\n```typescript\nexport function useSolPrice(): number | null {\n  const [price, setPrice] = useState<number | null>(null);\n  const intervalRef = useRef<ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null>(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    let cancelled = false;\n\n    async function fetchPrice() {\n      try {\n        const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/price/sol-usd`);\n        if (!res.ok) return;\n        const data: { price: number } = await res.json();\n        if (!cancelled) setPrice(data.price);\n      } catch {\n        // Graceful degradation — keep previous price or null\n      }\n    }\n\n    fetchPrice();\n    intervalRef.current = setInterval(fetchPrice, REFRESH_INTERVAL_MS);\n\n    return () => {\n      cancelled = true;\n      if (intervalRef.current) clearInterval(intervalRef.current);\n    };\n  }, []);\n\n  return price;\n}\n```\n\n**Example: `src/features/player-profile/hooks/useTransactions.ts`**\n```typescript\nexport function useTransactions(game?: string) {\n  const [transactions, setTransactions] = useState<Transaction[]>([]);\n  const [nextCursor, setNextCursor] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [loadingMore, setLoadingMore] = useState(false);\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchPage = useCallback(\n    async (cursor?: string) => {\n      const token = getAccessToken();\n      if (!token) {\n        setTransactions([]);\n        setLoading(false);\n        return;\n      }\n      // Fetch with JWT Bearer token\n      const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/profile/transactions?${qs}`, {\n        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n        signal: controller.signal,\n      });\n      // ...\n    },\n    [game],\n  );\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    fetchPage();\n    return () => abortRef.current?.abort();\n  }, [fetchPage]);\n\n  return { transactions, loading, loadingMore, error, nextCursor, loadMore };\n}\n```\n\n**Hook Export Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// features/player-profile/hooks/index.ts\nexport { usePlayerProfile, truncateAddress } from \"../context/PlayerProfileContext\";\nexport { useTransactions } from \"./useTransactions\";\nexport type { Transaction } from \"./useTransactions\";\nexport { useSolPrice } from \"./useSolPrice\";\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Context Provider Pattern\n\n**Example: `src/features/quests/context/QuestsContext.tsx`**\n\n```typescript\ninterface QuestsContextValue {\n  dailyQuests: QuestProgress[];\n  weeklyQuests: QuestProgress[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  dailyResetAt: number;\n  weeklyResetAt: number;\n  treasureChests: TreasureChest[];\n  unopenedChestCount: number;\n  claimableQuestCount: number;\n  chestDropNotification: ChestDropNotification;\n  claimQuestReward: (questId: string) => Promise<{ xp: number; chests: number }>;\n  openChest: (chestId: string) => Promise<ChestContents>;\n  openAllChests: () => Promise<ChestContents>;\n  // ... helper methods\n}\n\nexport function QuestsProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n  const { address } = useWallet(); // Access wallet address\n  \n  // State setup\n  const [dailyQuests, setDailyQuests] = useState<QuestProgress[]>([]);\n  // ... more state\n  \n  // Effects for loading and subscriptions\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!address) {\n      // Clear state when disconnected\n      return;\n    }\n    // Load data\n  }, [address]);\n  \n  const value: QuestsContextValue = { /* ... */ };\n  return (\n    <QuestsContext.Provider value={value}>\n      {children}\n    </QuestsContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\nexport function useQuests(): QuestsContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(QuestsContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useQuests must be used within QuestsProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Import Paths\n\n| Pattern | Import Path |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Session (auth, JWT) | `src/context/SessionContext` — `useSession()` |\n| Wallet (address, signing) | `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` — `useWallet()` |\n| Quests (main feature) | `src/features/quests` — `useQuests()`, `QuestsProvider` |\n| Profile (transactions, SOL price) | `src/features/player-profile/hooks` — `useTransactions()`, `useSolPrice()` |\n| Coinflip game | `src/features/coinflip` — `useCoinflip()` |\n| Toast CSS | `src/index.css` — `.rng-toast*` classes (line 3858+) |\n| Notification rendering | `src/App.tsx` AppContent — `<ChestDropNotification />` (line 372) |\n\n---\n\n### Key Patterns & Gotchas\n\n1. **Feature hooks live in `features/*/hooks/index.ts`** — they re-export from context or export custom data-fetching hooks\n2. **Contexts always check wallet connection** via `const { address } = useWallet()` and clear state when address is null\n3. **JWT token access:** Use `getAccessToken()` from `src/lib/auth-store` in custom hooks for Bearer tokens\n4. **Toasts are state-based, not imperative** — use context state to control visibility, not a toast library\n5. **Notifications are mounted globally in `App.tsx`** — not local to features\n6. **All contexts wrap error checking** — throw descriptive error if used outside provider\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/quests/context/QuestsContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/hooks/useTransactions.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/hooks/useSolPrice.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx` (main layout)"}],"totalDurationMs":88352,"totalTokens":62584,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":342,"cache_read_input_tokens":59356,"output_tokens":2880,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":342},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
